parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause injuries to occupants, distract the driver, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Airbag deployment without any collision or impact
deployment while driving at low or high speeds

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbags to Deploy in Crash
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: Airbags did not deploy in a crash
crash occurred at low or high speeds
crash involved a collision with an object or another vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inconsistent airbag deployment can lead to injuries or fatalities in certain crash scenarios.
symptoms: Airbags deployed in some crashes but not in others
airbags deployed on one side but not the other
airbags deployed in a non-crash scenario.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or jerk while shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the transmission makes a harsh sound
the vehicle is unable to engage into gear

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or lose power while accelerating, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when accelerating
the throttle body warning icon is illuminated
the engine RPM increases without accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the solenoid pack can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission makes a harsh sound
the vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the battery to drain, leading to difficulty starting the vehicle, which can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the horn does not work properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and entering limp mode can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle slows down or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body and Ignition Coil Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body and ignition coils can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to difficulty starting the vehicle, stalling, and loss of power.
symptoms: the throttle body and ignition coils need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the brake warning light can indicate a problem with the brake system, which can lead to accidents if not addressed.
symptoms: The brake warning light illuminates on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to enter "limp mode," reducing engine speed and power, which can lead to accidents, especially on highways. It can also cause the vehicle to stall, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle enters "limp mode" or "ETC engine failsafe mode
the check engine light is on
the vehicle accelerates slowly or erratically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coils can cause the engine to misfire, leading to reduced engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions.
symptoms: the check engine light is on
the vehicle accelerates slowly or erratically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective gas tank can cause gas leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and health problems.
symptoms: Gas smell inside or outside the vehicle
